         <abstract>
            <p>  From     <bibl corresp="http://zotero.org/groups/358366/items/S2FKU7VH"><seg type="encyclopediaArticle"><!-- attributes from original bibl--></seg><ptr target="bm:Lusini2005EAEDersanaS"/><title level="a">Dǝrsanä śǝllase</title><title type="short">EAe</title><title level="m">Encyclopaedia Aethiopica</title><author><forename>Gianfrancesco</forename><surname>Lusini</surname></author><editor><forename>Siegbert</forename><surname>Uhlig</surname></editor><pubPlace>Wiesbaden</pubPlace><publisher>Harrassowitz Verlag</publisher><date>2005</date><biblScope unit="volume">II</biblScope><biblScope unit="page">143a</biblScope><note type="tags"><note type="tag">bm:Lusini2005EAEDersanaS</note></note><note type="tag">bm:Lusini2005EAEDersanaS</note></bibl> (minimally rephrased): The homily is divided into 13 reading
            units, one for each month of the year. It is followed
            by a <ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2282Trinity">collection of miracles of the Trinity</ref>,
            and by a final doxology divided into seven reading-
            units, one for each day of the week.</p>
            <p>This work is attested in <ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/EMML150">Collegeville, Hill Museum and Manuscript Library, MS EMML no. 150</ref>, <ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/EMML1882">Collegeville, Hill Museum and Manuscript Library, MS EMML no. 1882</ref>
               and <ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/SHOr409">Hamburg, State and University Library Hamburg Carl von Ossietzky, Cod. orient. 409</ref>.</p>
         </abstract>
